Abdomen: Tergites with brownish setulae. Female abdomen: Single spermathecal duct uniformly thick, spermatheca vestigial. Paired spermathecal duct uniformly thick. Paired spermathecal duct stems with a small basal rounded swelling, apical half broad and striate before the spermathecae (
Fig. 71
). Paired spermathecae striate and oval, deeply invaginated from apex to base. Male abdomen: Ejaculatory apodeme bigger than epandrium and with a broad blade, wider than sperm pump (
Fig. 73
). Phallapodeme extending to anterior limit of hypandrium. Distiphallus long, longer than epandrium, ending in a phallic bulb, phallic bulb subequal in length and width.

